metadata.name: Patches #105
metadata.description:
This token generates a colorful abstract artwork that appears as watercolor on fabric. Project began as exploration of palettes used in famous masterpieces listed on Color Lisa web site. 97 color combinations used by great artists are applied here on abstract art.

Each piece is generated by bio inspired cellular automata in which colors from chosen palette are competing for domination on canvas. There are three different configurations of space fragmentation and each one is producing specific style.

metadata.name: Bipole #34
metadata.description:
Two meandering paths are created with opposite flow vectors. The paths are drawn with a twisty drip brush.

Created for #tezos4tezos in May 2022.

Features 
- The amount each stroke's bristles twist as the path is drawn
- If each paths starts off strong or soft
- Splats at the starts and ends of the path
- Dark mode
- Monochrome or colored lines (colors from the p5riso palette)
- Paper fibers in the background
- 10% chance of dark orange and black lines

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 2400px by 1483px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

metadata.name: FXHASH Generative Logo #988
metadata.description:
Unique iteration of the first Generative Token minted on fxhash.

It also servers as the actual logo of the platform. It represents the generative processes driving fxhash tokens. Generative Tokens are fed with a unique hash to produce unique outputs based on the hash — they are functions with a hash as single input.

The growth that comes out of the text is driven by a "Dividing-Aggregating Walkers" (DAW) algorithm. The hash drives all the DAW settings, as well as a mutation factor which is responsible for changes in each Walker parameters as they divide.

Some iterations will produce very simple outputs whereas others might be more chaotic.

Piece by @ciphrd for fxhash

metadata.name: Chaotic Growth #47
metadata.description:
Chaotic growth is based on a modified version of the differential line algorithm by Anders Hoff [1]. This algorithm uses an attraction-repulsion-model to imitate growth on a connected set of nodes. 

In this piece I explored an adaption of this algorithm attempting to visualize systems growing past their point of sustainability, creating new dynamics and eventually spiraling out of control. Some iterations may grow smoothly for some time but will quickly turn into a chaotic system of unsustainable growth. The smooth and organic shape of growth in the beginning is contrasted by the spikey, incoherent offshoots. 


Created in Vanilla JS.

Controls:
S - Save image
Space - Pause/Unpause


Best viewed in Chrome. Different browsers may produce slightly different outputs.

[1] https://inconvergent.net/generative/differential-line/

metadata.name: Euphonic #45
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moiré effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

metadata.name: DIƧPΛЯΛПDӨ BYƬΣƧ ΛӨ VΛZIӨ #19
metadata.description:
Conglomerados moleculares e polígonos complexos se subvertem em formas simplistas de pixels:
A força gravitacional é implacável até para o que não se comporta como partícula - as ondas e a própria gravidade se interfere.
Você consegue rever seu conceito definido de animação para o que parece um loop perfeito? Aqui as matemáticas aplicadas geram sequências numéricas nunca congruentes, possibilitando um caos nos encontros esperados pela ansiedade humana - afinal a mesma compreensão de um todo complexo pode ser alcançada através das sutileza da mente de preencher espaços não ocupados.

Não existe forma certa [o exato é relativo a individualidade da percepção].

[Estudo nº2/∞ que busca expandir nosso entendimento sobre a visão]

Desenvolvido em Hydra.js e implementado no p5.

metadata.name: Extreme Ways #350
metadata.description:
« Extreme ways are back again
Extreme places I didn't know
I broke everything new again
Everything that I'd owned
I threw it out the windows, came along
Extreme ways I know move apart The colors of my sea
Perfect color me… »
Song/Lyrics by Moby

All pieces are broken again and again…

Controls
Extreme ways contains some interactivity if you wish to explore.
Since this artwork is complex it takes time to draw, be patient. 

Press h in live mode to list the possibilities and see tips for interactivity usage.
Key ’s’  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key ‘c’ : Change colors
Key ‘m’ : Change main style
Key ‘d’ : Change drawing style
…
 

Pricing
Proposed as a Dutch Auction 11-9-7-5 tez with a step every 10 minutes.


Features
Main features are listed : Main style, drawing style, etc…
I do not think rarity will be a good indicator of the quality of the output.
Trust your taste and buy on the secondary what you like…
Lots of parameters are used internally to ensure a large variety in the outputs.

metadata.name: Copenhagen Interpretation #50
metadata.description:
The Copenhagen Interpretation of quantum physics suggests that objects don't have physical properties until being observed.

In this generative piece by itsgalo and Spøgelsesmaskinen, a set of objects are being held in "superposition" and finally positioned when observed and minted.

Use mouse/touch to zoom, pan, and rotate. Press 's' to grab a screenshot. Best viewed in Firefox.
